</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufinrazielthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FinrazielTheMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#333333>(10/14/02 9:19:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP Pet question..</span><hr size=1> <br>
Pets obtainable only at 61st-64th level should of course be better then a pet obtainable at level 50.  Thats how the game works.<br>
<br>
The Mage Epic Quest is very long, and very difficult and the reward is indeed nice and will serve as an awesome upgrade for any mage who gets it, but there is no reason for it not to be overshadowed by pets from the next tier of play.<br>
<br>
Thats what game progression is all about.  Many Epics are overshadowed, and most replaced long before the mage epic is.  If there will never be an upgrade to an item/pet obtainable at 50, progess is broken.<br>
<br>
My guess is that the PoP pets will be more powerful then the Epic Pet, but also more specialized, leaving the Epic Pet as still a great 'general purpose' pet.<br>
<br>
Sage Finraziel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufarieone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farieone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(10/14/02 11:30:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP Pet question..</span><hr size=1> Soooo Not true! They naturally need to revamp how pets work but.... Name a general situation against a general mob that any pet other than epic is more useful? none! Yeah sure your gonna whip out your fire for the firecasting mobs... and earth if you must have some form of root.. or you need to chain cast a powerful pet... but the magician epic pet fits well into every slot!<br>
<br>
So naturally the POP pets... in certain situations will be needed more than epic.. but nothing will replace clicking my orb!<br>
<br>
POP pets... yeah i might buy them.,. will i use them much? doubtful<br>
<br>
 they need to make pets more powerful with the lvl of the mage.. not the lvl of the spell.. <p><marquee>" Farieone Snowbunny * 59 Epic Magician * LaFamilia * FenninRo "</marquee></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzebanar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#333333>(10/15/02 2:44:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Here's what I expect...</span><hr size=1> I would expect each of the pets to out perform the epic in each of their respective areas..<br>
<br>
Water- Damage<br>
Earth- Mob control, HP<br>
Air- Stunning the mob. <br>
<br>
The epic would be still probably behave as the best solo pet, but wouldn't excel in groups as would say, the Air pets stun, or water pets damage. <br>
<br>
I think the above scenario would be best for ALL of us, the non-epiced mages and the epic magicians. We both need to gain from the new pets.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ushorttiie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shorttiie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(10/15/02 10:30:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's what I expect...</span><hr size=1> After everything I did to get my epic I would be pissed to have done that just be able to buy a spell off PoP vendor_01 which out does it. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88686"> ... </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualladdim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(10/15/02 5:57:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's what I expect...</span><hr size=1> Sure the epic pet is nice and all. But you're missing one point, Epic is supposed to be an optional quest for the class you're playing, it's NOT the BE ALL END ALL piece of equipment/spell. As you progressively get more powerful old equipment/spells tend to get obsolete. Look at the weapons from Vex Thal, they are ONE big step from most epics. Most of our warrior with epics in our guild would rather use a Fleshgrinder (from CT) to keep aggro than with their epics. Mage epic is tough to get, sure, but the pet is summoned without consuming mana or components plus the orb is a great 1HB item with great stats. Personally I would rather see the 61-65 pet to be greater/comparable to the epic.<br>
<br>
